Name: FATAL_V12
Description: V_12P0 not available / not detected / timeout. -> Check short on V_12P0, check powersupply, check V_EXT (R5R20, R5R19), check PSU_V12P0_EN (R9A2, R9B2)

Name: FATAL_V5
Description: V_5P0 not available / timeout. -> Check short on V_5P0, check U3E2, Q3E1, Q3E2 and surrounding resistors.

Name: FATAL_V3P3_PWRGPA
Description: PWRGPA timeout / not reporting PWRGD -> Check short on V_3P3, V_SOC1P8PLL, VMEMIOAB/CD, VTT[ABCD]. Pull VREG_PWRGPA_EN to V_3P3STBY manually and check V_3P3, V_SOC1P8PLL, VMEMIOAB/CD, (VTT[ABCD]) voltages.

Name: FATAL_CPUGFX_STARTUP_PWRGPB
Description: PWRGPB timeout / not reporting PWRGD -> Check short on V_FUSE, V_SOCPHY, V_NBCORE, V_MEMCORE. Pull VREG_PWRGPB_EN to V_3P3STBY manually and check V_FUSE, V_SOCPHY, V_NBCORE, V_MEMCORE voltages.

Name: FATAL_WIFI_UNRESET
Description: CPUGFX_PWRGD timeout / not reporting PWRGD -> Check short on V_CPUCORE, V_GFXCORE (they can be low resistance, dont confuse with a short!), check R9C64, U9D2, U9D3, U9D4, U9E1, U9E2 drivers, mosfets and U9C2.

Name: FATAL_SBPOWERUP1
Description: Wait for `SBPowerUp1(0)` to complete

Name: FATAL_GFXCPU_I2C_UNREACHABLE
Description: NCP4204 I2C unreachable -> Check R9C1, R9C2, surrounding traces, replace U9C2

Name: FATAL_MEMIOCD
Description: U6C1 I2C unreachable -> Check surrounding traces, replace U6C1

Name: BOOT_SBUNRESETWAIT
Description: SB (Southbridge) unreset wait finished

Name: BOOT_PSPBOOTACKWAIT_DONE
Description: Waiting for PSP Boot Acknowledge finished

Name: BOOT_PSPPORSPEWWAIT_DONE
Description: PSP Power-On Reset spew wait done

Name: BOOT_SOCUNRESETWAIT_DONE
Description: SOC unreset wait complete

Name: BOOT_SOCFLASHACCWAIT
Description: SOC flash access wait done

Name: BOOT_SOCPOST_DONE
Description: SOC POST (Power-On Self-Test) wait done

Name: BOOT_XSS_TIMEOUT_46
Description: XSS wait timeout (SOC not responding) - error fallback

Name: BOOT_XSS_TIMEOUT_47
Description: XSS wait timeout fallback path (word_20000090 nonzero)

Name: BOOT_SOCPOWEROK_DONE
Description: SOC power OK complete

Name: BOOT_COND_EARLY_ABORT
Description: Conditional POST on XSSActiveWait() return < 0 - XSS wait failed - early abort

Name: RESET_PSPACK_MISSING
Description: Unexpected PSP Boot Ack not received

Name: RESET_FATAL_THERMAL_PENDING
Description: Fatal or thermal error pending during wait

Name: RESET_TIMEOUT
Description: Reset wait timeout

Name: RESET_PIMACK_FAIL
Description: HandlePIMBootAck or response fails

Name: RESET_PIM_BOOT_INCOMPLETE
Description: PIM boot ack or early boot signal incomplete

Name: RESET_BITMASK_INVALID
Description: Bitmask condition not met (& 5 == 0)

Name: RESET_INVALID_STATE
Description: Invalid state detected

Name: RUNTIME_GET_SOCSyncFLOOD_STATE
Description: Triggered if SOC_SyncFlood() returns true

Name: RUNTIME
Description: Happens if sub_10001532 fails after repeated attempts maybe Timeout waiting for PCIe device

Name: RUNTIME
Description: PLL_Clk_Maybe() failed, likely clock not stable

Name: RUNTIME_GET_SBSystemSubmode
Description: Final PCIe init or handshake failure
